{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775842734457,"sessionID":"ses_2878688b6ffeo9bpkBg84IeBsN","part":{"id":"prt_d7879ad75001FCczhDfxU5M8d1","messageID":"msg_d78799b7b001VzRqcxwXdNEm3l","sessionID":"ses_2878688b6ffeo9bpkBg84IeBsN","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a5c0440bd9864a2b8b4498be","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-005\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: M\n13: - **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n18: \n19: ### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime resource in namespace \"default\" with valid TargetPorts and PodTemplate\n22: - **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/agentruntimes/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n23: - **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the AgentRuntime specification\n24: - **AND** SHALL create a Pod matching the PodTemplate specification\n25: - **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent AgentRuntime\n26: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n27: \n28: ### AR-005-002: Create Sandbox from CodeInterpreter\n29: \n30: - **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter resource in namespace \"default\" with valid Template configuration\n31: - **WHEN** a POST request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/default/codeinterpreters/{name}/sandbox` to create a new sandbox\n32: - **THEN** the handler SHALL parse the CodeInterpreter template specification\n33: - **AND** SHALL create a Pod using the ContainerTemplateSpec\n34: - **AND** SHALL apply warm pool logic if WarmPoolSize > 0\n35: - **AND** SHALL set appropriate labels to link the sandbox to the parent CodeInterpreter\n36: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 201 Created with sandbox identification information\n37: \n38: ### AR-005-003: Sandbox creation with custom parameters\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter resource\n41: - **WHEN** a POST request includes custom override parameters in the request body\n42: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the overrides to the sandbox specification\n43: - **AND** SHALL validate that override values meet validation constraints\n44: - **AND** SHALL merge overrides with the base template\n45: \n46: ### AR-005-004: Sandbox creation validation failure\n47: \n48: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with invalid PodTemplate (e.g., missing required container image)\n49: - **WHEN** a POST request attempts to create a sandbox\n50: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 400 Bad Request\n51: - **AND** SHALL include validation error details in the response\n52: \n53: ### AR-005-005: Sandbox creation for non-existent resource\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server\n56: - **WHEN** a POST request targets a non-existent AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter\n57: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 404 Not Found\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Scenario: Sandbox Lifecycle Management\n62: \n63: ### AR-005-010: Get Sandbox Status\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** a running HTTP server with active sandboxes\n66: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n67: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return the current sandbox status including:\n68:   - Pod phase (Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown)\n69:   - Container states\n70:   - IP address if assigned\n71:   - Creation timestamp\n72:   - Parent resource reference (AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter)\n73: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n74: \n75: ### AR-005-011: List Sandboxes\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances running in a namespace\n78: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes`\n79: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return a list of all sandboxes in the namespace\n80: - **AND** SHALL support labelSelector query parameter for filtering\n81: - **AND** SHALL include sandbox metadata and status summary\n82: \n83: ### AR-005-012: Delete Sandbox\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** an existing sandbox instance\n86: - **WHEN** a DELETE request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}`\n87: - **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate the sandbox Pod\n88: - **AND** SHALL clean up associated resources (services, configmaps)\n89: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK with deletion confirmation\n90: \n91: ### AR-005-013: Delete Sandbox with force option\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with terminating Pod that fails to stop gracefully\n94: - **WHEN** a DELETE request includes `gracePeriodSeconds=0` and `force=true`\n95: - **THEN** the handler SHALL forcefully terminate the sandbox\n96: - **AND** SHALL return HTTP 200 OK\n97: \n98: ### AR-005-014: Watch Sandboxes\n99: \n100: - **GIVEN** multiple sandbox instances\n101: - **WHEN** a GET request is sent to `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes?watch=true`\n102: - **THEN** the server SHALL stream sandbox events as NDJSON\n103: - **AND** SHALL send ADDED, MODIFIED, and DELETED events as sandboxes change state\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Scenario: Sandbox Template Processing\n108: \n109: ### AR-005-020: Process AgentRuntime PodTemplate\n110: \n111: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with a PodTemplate containing custom containers, volumes, and node selectors\n112: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this AgentRuntime\n113: - **THEN** the handler SHALL merge the PodTemplate.Spec with default values\n114: - **AND** SHALL apply the specified NodeSelector, Affinity, and Tolerations\n115: - **AND** SHALL preserve InitContainers if specified\n116: \n117: ### AR-005-021: Process CodeInterpreter ContainerTemplate\n118: \n119: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with a ContainerTemplate (image, command, args, env, resources)\n120: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox from this CodeInterpreter\n121: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Pod with a single container from the template\n122: - **AND** SHALL apply resource requirements from the template\n123: - **AND** SHALL set the RuntimeClassName if specified\n124: \n125: ### AR-005-022: Apply Security Context\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with SecurityContext configured\n128: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n129: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply PodSecurityContext to the Pod\n130: - **AND** SHALL apply SecurityContext to each container\n131: - **AND** SHALL validate security context values against policy\n132: \n133: ### AR-005-023: Inject Environment Variables\n134: \n135: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with Env variables in the template\n136: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n137: - **THEN** the handler SHALL inject the specified environment variables\n138: - **AND** SHALL support both static values and references (e.g., from secrets, configmaps)\n139: \n140: ---\n141: \n142: ## Scenario: Sandbox Pool Management\n143: \n144: ### AR-005-030: Warm Pool Pre-provisioning\n145: \n146: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize = 3\n147: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is created or becomes ready\n148: - **THEN** the handler SHALL proactively create 3 sandbox Pods\n149: - **AND** SHALL mark them as warm/ready\n150: - **AND** SHALL maintain the warm pool size\n151: \n152: ### AR-005-031: Warm Pool Scaling\n153: \n154: - **GIVEN** a warm pool with 3 ready sandboxes\n155: - **WHEN** a new sandbox request arrives and all warm sandboxes are in use\n156: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create an additional sandbox to handle the request\n157: - **AND** SHALL attempt to maintain the warm pool size\n158: \n159: ### AR-005-032: Warm Pool Cleanup\n160: \n161: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with WarmPoolSize reduced from 5 to 2\n162: - **WHEN** the pool size change is detected\n163: - **THEN** the handler SHALL terminate excess warm sandboxes\n164: - **AND** SHALL gracefully drain unused sandboxes first\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## Scenario: Sandbox Networking\n169: \n170: ### AR-005-040: Expose Sandbox Ports\n171: \n172: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts configured (port 8080, protocol HTTP)\n173: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n174: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a Service exposing the specified ports\n175: - **AND** SHALL set up appropriate network policies if configured\n176: - **AND** SHALL configure ingress routing based on PathPrefix\n177: \n178: ### AR-005-041: Sandbox Ingress Configuration\n179: \n180: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with TargetPorts including PathPrefix \"/api\"\n181: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n182: - **THEN** the handler SHALL configure ingress rules for the specified path\n183: - **AND** SHALL ensure the path prefix is routed to the correct container port\n184: \n185: ### AR-005-042: Network Policy Enforcement\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with network policy requirements\n188: - **WHEN** creating network resources\n189: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply NetworkPolicy resources to restrict traffic\n190: - **AND** SHALL support both ingress and egress rules\n191: \n192: ---\n193: \n194: ## Scenario: Sandbox Scheduling\n195: \n196: ### AR-005-050: Node Selection\n197: \n198: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with NodeSelector configured (disktype=ssd, region=us-west)\n199: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n200: - **THEN** the handler SHALL schedule the Pod on a node matching the node selectors\n201: - **AND** SHALL handle scheduling failures gracefully\n202: \n203: ### AR-005-051: Affinity and Anti-Affinity\n204: \n205: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with Affinity rules (podAntiAffinity, nodeAffinity)\n206: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n207: - **THEN** the handler SHALL apply the affinity rules to Pod scheduling\n208: - **AND** SHALL respect both required and preferred affinity rules\n209: \n210: ### AR-005-052: Resource Quota Enforcement\n211: \n212: - **GIVEN** a namespace with ResourceQuota limiting CPU, memory, or pod count\n213: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox exceeds quota\n214: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return HTTP 403 Forbidden\n215: - **AND** SHALL include quota violation details in the response\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Scenario: Error Handling and Recovery\n220: \n221: ### AR-005-060: Pod Creation Failure\n222: \n223: - **GIVEN** a sandbox creation request\n224: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API returns an error during Pod creation\n225: - **THEN** the handler SHALL return appropriate HTTP status code (4xx or 5xx)\n226: - **AND** SHALL include error message with cause details\n227: - **AND** SHALL log the error for debugging\n228: \n229: ### AR-005-061: Sandbox Status Sync\n230: \n231: - **GIVEN** a sandbox whose Pod has crashed or been killed externally\n232: - **WHEN** querying sandbox status\n233: - **THEN** the handler SHALL detect the stale state\n234: - **AND** SHALL update the sandbox status to reflect the actual Pod state\n235: - **AND** SHALL emit events for status changes\n236: \n237: ### AR-005-062: Graceful Shutdown\n238: \n239: - **GIVEN** a running sandbox\n240: - **WHEN** the WorkloadManager receives shutdown signal\n241: - **THEN** the handler SHALL not accept new sandbox requests\n242: - **AND** SHALL wait for in-flight sandbox creations to complete\n243: - **AND** SHALL not terminate existing sandboxes (responsibility of controller)\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## References\n248: \n249: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md`\n250: - Related AR: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架)\n251: - AgentRuntime CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n252: - CodeInterpreter CRD: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n253: - client-go library: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/client-go/`\n254: - API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n\n(End of file - total 254 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing the Sandbox creation handler in `pkg/workloadmanager`. The Sandbox creation handler is responsible for provisioning sandboxed execution environments based on AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter configurations.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-005\n- **Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Depends On**: AR-004 (WorkloadManager HTTP 服务框架), client-go library\n\n---\n\n## Scenario: Sandbox Resource Creation\n\n### AR-005-001: Create Sandbox from AgentRuntime\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775842734437,"end":1775842734454}}}}
